definitions.definition: To make something internal ; to incorporate it in oneself .

subdefinitions.definition: To process new information in one's mind.
To refrain from expressing (a negative emotion), to one's psychological detriment ; to bottle up .

definitions.definition: To store (a string or other structure) in a shared pool, such that subsequent items with the same value can share the same instance .
To transfer stocks between brokers within an organization , rather than through the exchange .

main_definition: ( transitive ) To make something internal ; to incorporate it in oneself .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive , programming ) To store (a string or other structure) in a shared pool, such that subsequent items with the same value can share the same instance .
( finance ) To transfer stocks between brokers within an organization , rather than through the exchange .
